definition: someone/people/anyone/there is someone there/occupied (as in restroom)
to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be
there are plenty of such people
to have qualified successors to carry on one's undertaking
in the wider world there are people more talented than oneself (idiom)
pinyin: ren2 wai4 you3 ren2 , tian1 wai4 you3 tian1

definition: see 人外有人，天外有天[ren2 wai4 you3 ren2 , tian1 wai4 you3 tian1]
pinyin: tian1 wai4 you3 tian1 , ren2 wai4 you3 ren2

sentences.english: Now, there are some immediate bad explanations for this.
sentences.chinese: 马上就有人提出一些错漏百出的解释。

sentences.english: Someone you least expect could be trying to make you look bad.
sentences.chinese: 有人可能会想让你出丑，这个人是你意想不到的。

sentences.english: Someone has stolen your treasure box.
sentences.chinese: 有人把你的珠宝盒给偷走了。

sentences.english: But recently some people presented a new algebraic diagonalization method.
sentences.chinese: 最近有人提出一种新的代数对角化方法。

sentences.english: I believe someone else suggested it would make a good doormat.
sentences.chinese: 也许会有人说不如把它放在门口做个地垫。

sentences.english: Second, the participation of non-owner occupied, such as housing loan or rental.
sentences.chinese: 二是让非所有人占有，如将房屋出借或出租。

sentences.english: Ylath never asked to be worshipped.
sentences.chinese: 伊拉斯从未寻求有人崇拜。

sentences.english: Everywhere they appeared they were ovations.
sentences.chinese: 他们所到之处都有人欢呼。

sentences.english: The population of New Zealand is now three million(s).
sentences.chinese: 新西兰现有人口三百万。

sentences.english: Just as if some one was kissing the window all over outside.
sentences.chinese: 就好像有人从外面把窗子吻了个遍。

sentences.english: In this age of the keyboard , some people seem to think handwriting lessons are on the way out.
sentences.chinese: 在这个键盘的年代，有人似乎认为书法课即将灭亡。

sentences.english: When all men think alike, no man thinks very much.
sentences.chinese: 除夜家皆一样念的时间便出有人多念了。

sentences.english: What if someone says something negative about me?
sentences.chinese: 如果有人说什么对我不利的东西呢？

sentences.english: Could someone stamp my frequent kidnapping card?
sentences.chinese: 有人可以给我的绑架集点卡盖章吗？

sentences.english: There must is someone who can take control of these naughty children.
sentences.chinese: 应该有人能管住这些淘气的孩子。

sentences.english: Some argue that it originates from the Zulu for 'making a loud noise'.
sentences.chinese: 有人说是来源于祖鲁语中“制造噪音”的说法。
